               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16891211-24-off108-c81" targOrder="Y" targets="t16891211-24-defend118 t16891211-24-off108 t16891211-24-verdict109"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16891211-24-defend118" type="defendantName">
                     Rowland 
                     Smith
                  <interp inst="t16891211-24-defend118" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-defend118" type="given" value="Rowland"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-defend118" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was Indicted for a Misdemeanor in <rs id="t16891211-24-off108" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-off108" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-off108" type="offenceSubcategory" value="fraud"></interp>
               Counterfeiting a Letter in the Name of one 
                     <persName id="t16891211-24-person119">
                        Elizabeth 
                        Blackerby
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-person119" type="surname" value="Blackerby"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16891211-24-person119" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16891211-24-person119" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , directed to one Mr. 
                     <persName id="t16891211-24-person120">Tho. Draper</persName>
                  , a Draper in Bishopsgate street, for divers Goods, as Holland, and other Linnens, &amp;c.
            </rs> The Letter was read in Court, which was, that Mrs. Blackerby desired that he would send immediately 2 or 3 pieces of Holland, and some other odd things: which Mr. Draper suspecting, sent to Mrs. Blackerby about it, and found it to be a Cheat: and she declared in Court, that she never sent for any Goods, neither writ any Letter, so he was found <rs id="t16891211-24-verdict109" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-verdict109" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs> of the Counterfeit.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16891211-24-punish110" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-punish110" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16891211-24-punish110" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="pillory"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t16891211-24-defend118 t16891211-24-punish110"></join>
               
                     <note>[Pillory. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
